articles.description: The National Arboretum's trees struggled to take root, and then were carefully kept alive through drought and bushfire. Now months of good rain has seen its forests explode into life.
articles.content:
The National Arboretum, which has been slowly taking root in Canberra for almost a decade, has seen its forests explode in growth after a deluge of rain this summer.
